<h2>System Reload</h2>


<table class="formtable">
	<tr>
		<td>
			Under certain circumstances, the administrator may be asked to perform a Software Reload, Software Restart, or Server Reboot, otherwise, it's recommended that you do not click these buttons. 
		</td>
	</tr>			
	<tr>
		<td>
			<button type="button">Software Reload</button> 
			<br/>
			<small>This reloads the configuration of the software without a restart. This will not drop any calls.</small>
		</td>
	</tr>

	<tr>
		<td>
			<button type="button">Software Restart</button> 	
			<br/>
			<small>This restarts all of the software on the PBX. This will drop all current calls. </small>
		</td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		<td>
			<button type="button">Server Reboot</button> 	
			<br/>
			<small>This will turn off your PBX and then turn it back on. This will drop all current calls. </small>
		</td>
	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		<td>
			<button type="button">Server Shutdown</button> 	
			<br/>
			<small>This will turn off your PBX. </small>
		</td>
	</tr>
	
</table>